      "message": "[Critical] Line 241: ensureDaemonStarted() can throw IllegalStateException when called from the daemon executor thread. That makes the push path crash instead of logging and safely dropping/retrying the push. Since push handling already treats startup failure as a recoverable condition, this should not use check(); return false and log the programming error, or guarantee at the call sites that this cannot happen.\n```suggestion\nif (onDaemonExecutor.get()) {\n    Log.e(TAG, \"ensureDaemonStarted must not be called from the DaemonExecutor thread\")\n    return false\n}\n```",
