      "message": "Line 324: onPushProcessed() decrements activePushCount but the counter is never used to control either the wakelock or the foreground-service lifetime. It can also become negative if calls ever get unbalanced. This is misleading state in a reliability-sensitive path. Either remove the counter or use it to release/stop when the last active push completes, with a floor guard.\n```suggestion\nval remaining \u003d activePushCount.updateAndGet { count -\u003e maxOf(0, count - 1) }\nLog.d(TAG, \"onPushProcessed: remaining\u003d$remaining\")\n```",
