      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 54: The same lifecycle bug exists for UnifiedPush: processing is launched in a PushService-owned scope and cancelled in onDestroy(), so Android can cancel JSON parsing/bootstrap/dispatch while the foreground service and wakelock are still active. Use an application-owned push processing scope or hand the work to PushForegroundService/WorkManager instead of cancelling it with the transient service instance.\n```suggestion\napp?.pushScope?.launch {\n    try {\n        val msgStr \u003d String(message.content, Charsets.UTF_8)\n        val obj \u003d JSONObject(msgStr)\n        val msg \u003d HashMap\u003cString, String\u003e()\n        obj.keys().forEach { msg[it] \u003d obj.getString(it) }\n        app.onMessage(msg)\n    } catch (e: Exception) {\n        Log.e(TAG, \"onMessage\", e)\n    } finally {\n        app.onPushProcessed()\n    }\n}\n```",
